              "explanation": "The submission clearly uses the diphoton invariant mass m_yy and provides a signal assessment, but it is not logically consistent with its own artifacts and does not satisfy the rubric\u2019s \u201cnear 125 GeV\u201d requirement. It claims a Higgs-like excess localized near 120 GeV, yet the residuals in the defined signal window (120\u2013130 GeV) are mostly negative, which contradicts the assertion of an excess there. The fitted Gaussian mean at 120.0 GeV is also not supported by a coherent positive residual structure in that region. Moreover, the residual-uncertainty treatment is inconsistent with the stated method: a bin with zero counts (110 GeV) is assigned an uncertainty of 1.0 instead of sqrt(0)=0. Finally, the narrative does not explicitly assess the presence/absence of an excess near 125 GeV; it centers on 120 GeV instead. Due to these inconsistencies and the unmet \u201cnear 125 GeV\u201d assessment, the submission does not pass.",
